<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-13660] Replace log4j with reload4j</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-13660</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Kafka is using a known vulnerable version of log4j, the reload4j project was created by the code&apos;s original authors to address those issues. It is designed as a drop in replacement without any api changes&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://reload4j.qos.ch/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://reload4j.qos.ch/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve raised a merge request, replacing log4j with reload4j, slf4j-log4j12 with slf4j-reload4j and bumping the slf4j version&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is my first time contributing to the Kafka project and I&apos;m not too familiar with the process, I&apos;ll go back and amend my PR with this issue number&lt;/p&gt;</description>
